WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.946 align:middle line:90%


00:00:08.946 --> 00:00:12.425 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:12.425 --> 00:00:24.738 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.738 --> 00:00:26.530 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:26.530 --> 00:00:28.920 align:middle line:84%
Our next guest is someone
very special to all of us

00:00:28.920 --> 00:00:29.920 align:middle line:90%
here at "Beyond Belief."

00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:33.010 align:middle line:10%
Dr. Eben Alexander,
a neurosurgeon

00:00:33.010 --> 00:00:36.070 align:middle line:10%
who had a remarkable
near-death experience that

00:00:36.070 --> 00:00:38.620 align:middle line:10%
not only changed his
life, but changed

00:00:38.620 --> 00:00:41.740 align:middle line:10%
the life of so many other
people because he wrote

00:00:41.740 --> 00:00:44.890 align:middle line:10%
several bestselling books,
including "Proof of Heaven,"

00:00:44.890 --> 00:00:47.657 align:middle line:10%
"The Map of Heaven," and
"Living in a Mindful Universe."

00:00:47.657 --> 00:00:49.240 align:middle line:10%
Eben, welcome back
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:50.810 align:middle line:84%
>>EBEN ALEXANDER: Well,
George, it's great to be here.

00:00:50.810 --> 00:00:52.018 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for having me back on.

00:00:52.018 --> 00:00:55.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I am not kidding,
because your experience,

00:00:55.090 --> 00:00:57.250 align:middle line:84%
and the way you
came forward with it

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:01.960 align:middle line:84%
was so remarkable and so
persuasive, it, I think,

00:01:01.960 --> 00:01:03.790 align:middle line:84%
changed the lives
of a lot of people

00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:07.720 align:middle line:84%
who were skeptical
about life after death.

00:01:07.720 --> 00:01:09.160 align:middle line:90%
You changed a lot of people.

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:11.890 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: Well, I think
that's very reassuring.

00:01:11.890 --> 00:01:15.250 align:middle line:84%
I was very skeptical
before my NDE.

00:01:15.250 --> 00:01:18.310 align:middle line:10%
So having that personal
experience and evidence,

00:01:18.310 --> 00:01:21.940 align:middle line:10%
like millions of others
have, helped us to wake

00:01:21.940 --> 00:01:24.110 align:middle line:10%
up to a bigger reality.

00:01:24.110 --> 00:01:27.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think as a
scientist, I am one

00:01:27.160 --> 00:01:29.170 align:middle line:84%
who is fascinated by
consciousness and brain

00:01:29.170 --> 00:01:32.140 align:middle line:84%
and mind, this is a very
natural thing for me

00:01:32.140 --> 00:01:33.410 align:middle line:90%
to be going through.

00:01:33.410 --> 00:01:35.650 align:middle line:84%
And my NDE, when I
look back on my life,

00:01:35.650 --> 00:01:37.570 align:middle line:84%
makes perfect sense
that that is what

00:01:37.570 --> 00:01:40.900 align:middle line:84%
would happen when I was
54 years old and trying

00:01:40.900 --> 00:01:43.420 align:middle line:84%
to find out some deeper
answers about the universe.

00:01:43.420 --> 00:01:45.460 align:middle line:84%
And the good news
is a lot of what

00:01:45.460 --> 00:01:48.400 align:middle line:84%
I've discovered and in work
with fellow scientists studying

00:01:48.400 --> 00:01:50.500 align:middle line:84%
consciousness, is
something that rings

00:01:50.500 --> 00:01:51.930 align:middle line:90%
true with many, many souls.

00:01:51.930 --> 00:01:55.030 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's
very positive that you

00:01:55.030 --> 00:01:57.985 align:middle line:84%
get that kind of feedback
about our interactions.

00:01:57.985 --> 00:01:59.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Huge.

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:01.270 align:middle line:84%
Let's build up to the
near-death experience.

00:02:01.270 --> 00:02:02.450 align:middle line:90%
What happened to you?

00:02:02.450 --> 00:02:04.700 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: Well, I think
it's important to point out

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:07.570 align:middle line:84%
at that time I was a 54-year-old
academic neurosurgeon

00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:09.880 align:middle line:84%
and spent more than 15 years
at Harvard Medical School

00:02:09.880 --> 00:02:12.520 align:middle line:84%
teaching, thinking I knew
something about brain, mind,

00:02:12.520 --> 00:02:13.600 align:middle line:90%
and consciousness.

00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:14.690 align:middle line:90%
And then very suddenly.

00:02:14.690 --> 00:02:17.470 align:middle line:90%
I was driven deep into coma.

00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:19.930 align:middle line:10%
The medical details
of my case are

00:02:19.930 --> 00:02:22.090 align:middle line:10%
available to anyone
who cares to look.

00:02:22.090 --> 00:02:25.540 align:middle line:84%
They were just
published September 2018

00:02:25.540 --> 00:02:27.880 align:middle line:84%
in the "Journal of Nervous
and Mental Diseases."

00:02:27.880 --> 00:02:29.670 align:middle line:84%
And that case report
is very important.

00:02:29.670 --> 00:02:32.740 align:middle line:84%
It was made by three
independent physicians

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:35.200 align:middle line:90%
who were not part of my care.

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:39.640 align:middle line:84%
And they note the extraordinary
nature of my illness--

00:02:39.640 --> 00:02:43.218 align:middle line:84%
that I should have had no robust
conscious experience at all.

00:02:43.218 --> 00:02:45.010 align:middle line:84%
I should have had
basically nothing because

00:02:45.010 --> 00:02:46.960 align:middle line:90%
of the damage to my neocortex.

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:50.320 align:middle line:84%
That's why my disease is
such a beautiful gift,

00:02:50.320 --> 00:02:54.010 align:middle line:84%
because it
obliterates the notion

00:02:54.010 --> 00:02:58.540 align:middle line:84%
that the physical brain is
what creates consciousness out

00:02:58.540 --> 00:02:59.650 align:middle line:90%
of nothing.

00:02:59.650 --> 00:03:01.750 align:middle line:84%
And that's where everybody
misses the point.

00:03:01.750 --> 00:03:04.540 align:middle line:84%
That's where the
modern science is going

00:03:04.540 --> 00:03:05.860 align:middle line:90%
in a very beautiful direction.

00:03:05.860 --> 00:03:08.770 align:middle line:84%
But to cut to the chase,
the experience itself

00:03:08.770 --> 00:03:11.890 align:middle line:84%
started in an ugly
underground realm--

00:03:11.890 --> 00:03:13.570 align:middle line:90%
the earthworm's eye view.

00:03:13.570 --> 00:03:16.960 align:middle line:10%
I was rescued from that by this
slowly spinning white light

00:03:16.960 --> 00:03:19.480 align:middle line:10%
with a perfect musical
melody that took me up

00:03:19.480 --> 00:03:23.170 align:middle line:10%
into the brilliant ultra-real
gateway valley, that

00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:24.770 align:middle line:10%
was very Earth-like
in many ways,

00:03:24.770 --> 00:03:28.058 align:middle line:10%
but also had strong
spiritual features.

00:03:28.058 --> 00:03:30.100 align:middle line:10%
And all this, of course,
is described in my book,

00:03:30.100 --> 00:03:31.660 align:middle line:10%
"Proof of Heaven."

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:34.300 align:middle line:84%
And there was a beautiful
guardian angel on a butterfly

00:03:34.300 --> 00:03:36.080 align:middle line:90%
wing in that realm--

00:03:36.080 --> 00:03:37.210 align:middle line:90%
in that gateway realm--

00:03:37.210 --> 00:03:40.840 align:middle line:84%
who proved extraordinarily
important many months later,

00:03:40.840 --> 00:03:43.060 align:middle line:84%
because it was her
identity that helped

00:03:43.060 --> 00:03:47.040 align:middle line:84%
me to come to realize
the very realistic nature

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:49.420 align:middle line:84%
and important
aspect of my journey

00:03:49.420 --> 00:03:52.930 align:middle line:84%
in terms of my life lessons
and what I was here to learn.

00:03:52.930 --> 00:03:55.870 align:middle line:84%
But that gateway valley
was only a stepping stone

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:59.530 align:middle line:84%
to even higher levels that I
visited in my NDE, all the way

00:03:59.530 --> 00:04:01.420 align:middle line:90%
out to what I call the core.

00:04:01.420 --> 00:04:03.830 align:middle line:84%
The core was infinite
inky blackness,

00:04:03.830 --> 00:04:07.300 align:middle line:84%
but filled to overflowing
with this brilliant light.

00:04:07.300 --> 00:04:09.170 align:middle line:90%
I called it a dazzling darkness.

00:04:09.170 --> 00:04:10.480 align:middle line:90%
It's filled with paradox.

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:13.690 align:middle line:84%
But that's because that's
where all the duality is--

00:04:13.690 --> 00:04:16.579 align:middle line:84%
good, bad, black,
white, male, female--

00:04:16.579 --> 00:04:20.110 align:middle line:84%
whatever the dualities of this
world come together as one.

00:04:20.110 --> 00:04:22.720 align:middle line:84%
And also, that's
where I witnessed

00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:24.790 align:middle line:84%
the pure oneness
of consciousness

00:04:24.790 --> 00:04:27.400 align:middle line:84%
and the origin of our
very conscious awareness

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:29.590 align:middle line:84%
with that God force--
the creative source

00:04:29.590 --> 00:04:31.420 align:middle line:90%
of the whole universe.

00:04:31.420 --> 00:04:33.730 align:middle line:84%
And there are other
features of that story that

00:04:33.730 --> 00:04:36.790 align:middle line:84%
are important in terms of the
scientific implications that

00:04:36.790 --> 00:04:40.690 align:middle line:84%
helped me to realize the
absolute reality of this.

00:04:40.690 --> 00:04:43.780 align:middle line:84%
All in the setting when my
doctors had perfect evidence

00:04:43.780 --> 00:04:47.020 align:middle line:84%
from my neurologic
exams, CT and MRI scans,

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:49.720 align:middle line:84%
lab values, that this
seven days spent deep

00:04:49.720 --> 00:04:53.320 align:middle line:84%
in coma due to a
very rare E. coli

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:56.020 align:middle line:84%
bacterial meningitis,
which almost always happens

00:04:56.020 --> 00:04:56.860 align:middle line:90%
in newborns.

00:04:56.860 --> 00:04:59.680 align:middle line:84%
Very rare to have E.
coli meningitis in anyone

00:04:59.680 --> 00:05:01.340 align:middle line:90%
older than three months.

00:05:01.340 --> 00:05:03.880 align:middle line:84%
So yes, I do have to defend
my level of maturity.

00:05:03.880 --> 00:05:07.660 align:middle line:84%
But the bottom line is
the whole experience

00:05:07.660 --> 00:05:11.210 align:middle line:84%
showed me the brain is not
the producer of consciousness.

00:05:11.210 --> 00:05:15.340 align:middle line:84%
When we die, we are actually
liberated to a far higher level

00:05:15.340 --> 00:05:18.340 align:middle line:84%
of awareness, as near-death
experiencers have been telling

00:05:18.340 --> 00:05:20.800 align:middle line:90%
us for thousands of years.

00:05:20.800 --> 00:05:23.470 align:middle line:84%
And so it was an
extraordinary gift.

00:05:23.470 --> 00:05:27.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How dramatic
did it change your life

00:05:27.050 --> 00:05:28.483 align:middle line:90%
when you came out of that coma?

00:05:28.483 --> 00:05:30.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: Well, it's
important to point out

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:32.770 align:middle line:84%
that one of the essential
features of my journey

00:05:32.770 --> 00:05:36.160 align:middle line:84%
that seemed very
strange at first,

00:05:36.160 --> 00:05:38.830 align:middle line:84%
and it's atypical for a
near-death experience,

00:05:38.830 --> 00:05:40.810 align:middle line:90%
is the fact that I was amnesic.

00:05:40.810 --> 00:05:44.590 align:middle line:84%
I had absolutely no words,
language, no memories of Earth,

00:05:44.590 --> 00:05:47.020 align:middle line:84%
of being human, and
certainly, no knowledge

00:05:47.020 --> 00:05:48.430 align:middle line:90%
of Eben Alexander's life.

00:05:48.430 --> 00:05:50.450 align:middle line:84%
That's the world
my NDE lived in.

00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:51.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: My gosh.

00:05:51.250 --> 00:05:53.470 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: Was a
complete empty slate.

00:05:53.470 --> 00:05:56.590 align:middle line:84%
And it took me months and
months after I came back

00:05:56.590 --> 00:05:59.170 align:middle line:84%
to realize why that
was so important.

00:05:59.170 --> 00:06:01.570 align:middle line:84%
Now, that effect
was so powerful,

00:06:01.570 --> 00:06:03.730 align:middle line:84%
that when I did come
back to this world on day

00:06:03.730 --> 00:06:09.070 align:middle line:84%
seven of my coma, my brain
was an absolute wreck.

00:06:09.070 --> 00:06:12.220 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even recognize
loved ones at the bedside--

00:06:12.220 --> 00:06:13.635 align:middle line:90%
my mother, my sisters, my son--

00:06:13.635 --> 00:06:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You mean
in reality now?

00:06:15.010 --> 00:06:17.343 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: In reality, when
I came back to this world,

00:06:17.343 --> 00:06:19.900 align:middle line:90%
I had no idea who they were.

00:06:19.900 --> 00:06:22.340 align:middle line:84%
And those memories
came back very quickly.

00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:24.970 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even have words
or language, as I said.

00:06:24.970 --> 00:06:27.850 align:middle line:84%
But words came back
literally within hours.

00:06:27.850 --> 00:06:30.730 align:middle line:84%
Much of my language was
completely back within a day.

00:06:30.730 --> 00:06:33.890 align:middle line:84%
Childhood memories returned
within a few weeks.

00:06:33.890 --> 00:06:37.540 align:middle line:10%
And the shocker, as I discuss
in detail in our third book,

00:06:37.540 --> 00:06:39.790 align:middle line:10%
"Living in a Mindful
Universe," is that really

00:06:39.790 --> 00:06:43.200 align:middle line:10%
by about two months after
coma all of my memories

00:06:43.200 --> 00:06:44.000 align:middle line:10%
had returned.

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:47.513 align:middle line:84%
All of my semantic knowledge of
cosmology, physics, chemistry,

00:06:47.513 --> 00:06:48.430 align:middle line:90%
biology, neuroscience.

00:06:48.430 --> 00:06:49.263 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Remarkable.

00:06:49.263 --> 00:06:50.847 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: Everything
had come back.

00:06:50.847 --> 00:06:52.390 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of my
personal memories--

00:06:52.390 --> 00:06:55.480 align:middle line:84%
and this was gleaned through
conversations with family

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:58.540 align:middle line:84%
and friends that mimic
conversations that had happened

00:06:58.540 --> 00:07:00.010 align:middle line:90%
years before my coma--

00:07:00.010 --> 00:07:03.640 align:middle line:84%
I realized the memories
were more complete

00:07:03.640 --> 00:07:04.780 align:middle line:90%
after I came back--

00:07:04.780 --> 00:07:07.770 align:middle line:84%
after they came back by
two months post-coma--

00:07:07.770 --> 00:07:08.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's unusual.

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:10.478 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: --than
they had been before.

00:07:10.478 --> 00:07:12.700 align:middle line:84%
It's not only unusual, it's
completely inexplicable

00:07:12.700 --> 00:07:16.630 align:middle line:84%
if you think that memories are
stored in the physical brain.

00:07:16.630 --> 00:07:19.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Eben, when you shut
down a computer the wrong way,

00:07:19.090 --> 00:07:21.190 align:middle line:90%
you could lose memory.

00:07:21.190 --> 00:07:24.580 align:middle line:84%
In your particular case, you
shut down in the wrong way,

00:07:24.580 --> 00:07:25.390 align:middle line:90%
too.

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:26.680 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: I guess you
can call it the wrong way.

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:29.178 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why didn't it just
wipe out memory totally?

00:07:29.178 --> 00:07:30.970 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: Well, see,
I think that's part

00:07:30.970 --> 00:07:35.020 align:middle line:84%
of the lesson is when I woke up
after this incredible journey

00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:38.500 align:middle line:84%
that would be impossible by
our modern neuroscientific

00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:41.350 align:middle line:84%
assessment of the
role of the neocortex

00:07:41.350 --> 00:07:44.500 align:middle line:90%
in human conscious awareness.

00:07:44.500 --> 00:07:47.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, really it violated
all those principles.

00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:49.330 align:middle line:84%
And so initially,
my thinking was,

00:07:49.330 --> 00:07:51.880 align:middle line:84%
as I was trying to
figure all this out,

00:07:51.880 --> 00:07:56.560 align:middle line:84%
I defaulted to my pre-coma
neurosurgical view of,

00:07:56.560 --> 00:08:00.850 align:middle line:84%
well, maybe that's why those
memories were so wrecked

00:08:00.850 --> 00:08:03.340 align:middle line:84%
during my coma was
because of this disruption

00:08:03.340 --> 00:08:04.390 align:middle line:90%
of the neocortex.

00:08:04.390 --> 00:08:06.200 align:middle line:84%
But then you have
to ask how come

00:08:06.200 --> 00:08:09.257 align:middle line:84%
they came back so completely,
even more complete than before?

00:08:09.257 --> 00:08:10.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or more so.

00:08:10.090 --> 00:08:10.890 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:10.890 --> 00:08:13.660 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: And the one
point I will make here

00:08:13.660 --> 00:08:16.570 align:middle line:84%
is, as much as people like
to believe that memories are

00:08:16.570 --> 00:08:18.070 align:middle line:84%
stored in the brain,
one thing we've

00:08:18.070 --> 00:08:20.753 align:middle line:84%
suspected for a long
time in neurosurgery--

00:08:20.753 --> 00:08:23.170 align:middle line:84%
and we don't talk about it
much, because everybody is kind

00:08:23.170 --> 00:08:26.860 align:middle line:84%
of a physicalist, materialist,
conventional scientist

00:08:26.860 --> 00:08:29.560 align:middle line:84%
by training-- but that is
that no matter what we've

00:08:29.560 --> 00:08:33.620 align:middle line:84%
done in resecting parts of the
brain over more than 100 years,

00:08:33.620 --> 00:08:35.770 align:middle line:84%
there's never been
a case where you had

00:08:35.770 --> 00:08:38.440 align:middle line:84%
identifiable swathes
of memory that were

00:08:38.440 --> 00:08:40.942 align:middle line:90%
gone with the resected brain.

00:08:40.942 --> 00:08:42.400 align:middle line:84%
That's something
else we talk about

00:08:42.400 --> 00:08:43.690 align:middle line:84%
in "Living in a
Mindful Universe."

00:08:43.690 --> 00:08:45.232 align:middle line:84%
I talk, in particular,
about the work

00:08:45.232 --> 00:08:48.640 align:middle line:84%
of Wilder Penfield, one of the
most renowned neurosurgeons

00:08:48.640 --> 00:08:50.540 align:middle line:90%
in the 20th century.

00:08:50.540 --> 00:08:52.370 align:middle line:84%
He worked in
Canada, in Montreal.

00:08:52.370 --> 00:08:55.540 align:middle line:84%
He wrote a beautiful
book in 1975

00:08:55.540 --> 00:09:00.310 align:middle line:84%
that summarized his life career
in electrical stimulation

00:09:00.310 --> 00:09:01.720 align:middle line:90%
of the brain in awake patients.

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:04.415 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's the most direct
way of assessing the mind brain

00:09:04.415 --> 00:09:05.215 align:middle line:90%
interface.

00:09:05.215 --> 00:09:06.340 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's remarkable.

00:09:06.340 --> 00:09:09.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ALEXANDER: And his book,
"Mystery of the Mind," 1975,

00:09:09.400 --> 00:09:11.620 align:middle line:90%
makes it very, very clear.

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:14.960 align:middle line:84%
The brain does not
produce consciousness.

00:09:14.960 --> 00:09:16.330 align:middle line:90%
It's a filter.

00:09:16.330 --> 00:09:17.770 align:middle line:90%
It allows consciousness in.

00:09:17.770 --> 00:09:20.867 align:middle line:84%
But Penfield came to
realize that memories--

00:09:20.867 --> 00:09:23.200 align:middle line:84%
he thought they were stored
in the neocortex originally,

00:09:23.200 --> 00:09:26.030 align:middle line:84%
but then he had plenty of
evidence that's not the case.

00:09:26.030 --> 00:09:28.450 align:middle line:84%
And by the end of
the day, it's very

00:09:28.450 --> 00:09:31.870 align:middle line:84%
clear to modern
neurosurgeons that memories

