00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:19.790 align:middle line:10%
- In quantum physics,
we talk about there

00:12:19.790 --> 00:12:23.270 align:middle line:10%
being many simultaneous
possibilities and probabilities

00:12:23.270 --> 00:12:25.760 align:middle line:10%
all existing at once.

00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:29.630 align:middle line:10%
Until a measurement
or observation, a.k.a.

00:12:29.630 --> 00:12:31.960 align:middle line:10%
a choice, is made.

00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:34.880 align:middle line:10%
Now, upon observation,
one of those possibilities

00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:38.400 align:middle line:10%
will manifest out while
the others will disappear.

00:12:38.400 --> 00:12:40.280 align:middle line:10%
This is known as
the observer effect

00:12:40.280 --> 00:12:42.620 align:middle line:10%
and collapsing the wave form.

00:12:42.620 --> 00:12:45.530 align:middle line:10%
How is this observer
effect discovered?

00:12:45.530 --> 00:12:48.200 align:middle line:10%
It relates to another
aspect of complementarity

00:12:48.200 --> 00:12:51.230 align:middle line:10%
known as wave particle duality.

00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:53.570 align:middle line:10%
In the early days of
quantum discovery,

00:12:53.570 --> 00:12:56.180 align:middle line:10%
it began with scientists
trying to understand

00:12:56.180 --> 00:12:58.160 align:middle line:10%
the nature of light.

00:12:58.160 --> 00:13:01.250 align:middle line:10%
Is it a wave or
is it a particle?

00:13:01.250 --> 00:13:04.700 align:middle line:10%
It turns out light
displays both behaviors.

00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:09.110 align:middle line:10%
Now, this confronted scientists
with a mystery, or a paradox.

00:13:09.110 --> 00:13:13.020 align:middle line:10%
How can might be both
a wave and a particle?

00:13:13.020 --> 00:13:18.100 align:middle line:10%
The paradigm at the time said it
must be either/or not both/and.

00:13:18.100 --> 00:13:20.420 align:middle line:10%
And the mystery
grew when scientists

00:13:20.420 --> 00:13:24.530 align:middle line:10%
began to wonder whether matter
also could behave as both wave

00:13:24.530 --> 00:13:25.700 align:middle line:10%
and particle.

00:13:25.700 --> 00:13:27.710 align:middle line:10%
And indeed, it could.

00:13:27.710 --> 00:13:30.410 align:middle line:10%
There have been many
indications and new discoveries

00:13:30.410 --> 00:13:33.600 align:middle line:10%
in quantum physics that
have confirmed all of this.

00:13:33.600 --> 00:13:37.370 align:middle line:10%
Now, to make a long story short,
if they set up the experiment

00:13:37.370 --> 00:13:39.890 align:middle line:10%
to see if it's a wave,
then indeed, they

00:13:39.890 --> 00:13:41.570 align:middle line:10%
get wave-like behavior.

00:13:41.570 --> 00:13:43.100 align:middle line:10%
But if they set
up the experiment

00:13:43.100 --> 00:13:45.530 align:middle line:10%
to try and observe
it as a particle,

00:13:45.530 --> 00:13:48.350 align:middle line:10%
then the behavior changes
to that of a particle.

00:13:48.350 --> 00:13:50.660 align:middle line:10%
It's all about how
the scientists choose

00:13:50.660 --> 00:13:53.885 align:middle line:10%
to set up their observation
or measurement points.

00:13:53.885 --> 00:13:56.180 align:middle line:10%
And what's
fascinating is that it

00:13:56.180 --> 00:14:00.780 align:middle line:10%
is as if the quanta are aware
that they're being observed.

00:14:00.780 --> 00:14:04.130 align:middle line:10%
The very act of observing
has a dramatic effect

00:14:04.130 --> 00:14:05.630 align:middle line:10%
on their behavior.

00:14:05.630 --> 00:14:08.040 align:middle line:10%
It is a real phenomenon.

